The paper deals with the problem of combining classifier ensembles for binary classification, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper also formulates the problem as a game played over a set of unlabeled data, which is a common approach in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
